{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Genealogy from Benjamin to Saul"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Benjamin was the father of Bela, his firstborn; Ashbel was the second born, Aharah the third,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Nohah the fourth, and Rapha the fifth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Bela:\nAddar, Gera, Abihud,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Gera, Shephuphan, and Huram."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These were the descendants of Ehud who were the heads of the families living in Geba and were exiled to Manahath:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera, who carried them into exile and who was the father of Uzza and Ahihud."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Shaharaim had sons in the country of Moab after he had divorced his wives Hushim and Baara."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "His sons by his wife Hodesh:\nJobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jeuz, Sachia, and Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of families."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He also had sons by Hushim:\nAbitub and Elpaal."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Elpaal:\nEber, Misham, Shemed (who built Ono and Lod with its villages),"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and Beriah and Shema (who were the heads of families of the inhabitants of Aijalon and who drove out the inhabitants of Gath)."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ahio, Shashak, Jeremoth,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Zebadiah, Arad, Eder,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Michael, Ishpah, and Joha were the sons of Beriah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ishmerai, Izliah, and Jobab were the sons of Elpaal."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jakim, Zichri, Zabdi,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Adaiah, Beraiah, and Shimrath were the sons of Shimei."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ishpan, Eber, Eliel,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Abdon, Zichri, Hanan,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Iphdeiah, and Penuel were the sons of Shashak."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jaareshiah, Elijah, and Zichri were the sons of Jeroham."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "All these were heads of families, the chiefs according to their genealogies, and they lived in Jerusalem."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jeiel the father of Gibeon lived in Gibeon. His wife’s name was Maacah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and Abdon was his firstborn son, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Nadab,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Gedor, Ahio, Zecher,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and Mikloth, who was the father of Shimeah. These also lived alongside their relatives in Jerusalem."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The Family of Saul"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "Ner was the father of Kish, Kish was the father of Saul, and Saul was the father of Jonathan, Malchishua, Abinadab, and Esh-baal."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "The son of Jonathan:\nMerib-baal, and Merib-baal was the father of Micah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Micah:\nPithon, Melech, Tarea, and Ahaz."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "36",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "Ahaz was the father of Jehoaddah, Jehoaddah was the father of Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri, and Zimri was the father of Moza."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "37",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Moza was the father of Binea. Raphah was his son, Eleasah his son, and Azel his son."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "38",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Azel had six sons, and these were their names:\nAzrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. All these were the sons of Azel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "39",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of his brother Eshek:\nUlam was his firstborn, Jeush second, and Eliphelet third."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "40",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Ulam were mighty men of valor, archers, and they had many sons and grandsons—150 in all.\nAll these were the descendants of Benjamin."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}